column5: as long it doesn't show too much rain tomorrow, i should be there for a few hours, till around 1pm.  going to catch the 8:45 ferry to wards island and then working over towards centre island. if anyone sees me, i'll be the lonely guy using a curado baitcaster.
Just wondering do you bus there or drive there? And if you drive is there a place that you can drop off the car?

I don't think I've ever seen free parking downtown...There are numerous pay parking lots around the area though.  I've always taken the TTC to the Islands except on one occasion where we parked the car at the lot at the bottom of Yonge st (I think)...It might have been around $8-10 to park for the day (I think)
Have a great day Kevin, should be a good day weather wise for the msot part  Maureen
lonely guy at the island? .. at least your fishing ... if you want to find me, i'd be the lonely guy sitting in a classroom lol.  good luck tomorrow and let us know how u make out!
I might show up with someone else too if they can wake up early. You never know. I might be on the 7am - 7:30am ferry wards.   dsn
